A PAL Compiler for CMPUT 415.

Team Meow
- Steve Jahns
- Mike Armstrong
- Chris Pavlicek
- Connor Moreside

To build, run:

	$ make

from the root dir, which will place the pal compiler executable at
	
	./bin/pal

To build and run all tests:

	$ make test

To build and run specific tests:
	
	$ make ScannerTest
	$ make ParserTest
	$ make ParserTestWithFiles

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PAL Sources
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	./src/main.cpp
		- driver program for compiler class

	./src/Compiler.cpp
	./src/Compiler.hpp
		- main compiler class

	./src/pal.lex
		- flex lexer source

	./src/Scanner.hpp
		- wrapper class for combined lexer + parser

	./src/pal.y
		- bison parser source

	./src/Parser.cpp
	./src/Parser.hpp
		- wrapper class for combined lexer + parser

	./src/Error.cpp
	./src/Error.hpp
		- error representation

	./src/ErrorCodes.hpp
		- defines all error types the compiler can find

	./src/ErrorManager.cpp
	./src/ErrorManager.hpp
		- tracks errors through the course of the compiler's execution

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Testing Sources
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

	./test/ParserTest.cpp
		- PalParser unit tests

	./test/ScannerTest.cpp
		- PalScanner unit tests

	./test/ParserTestWithFiles.cpp
		- Full parser tests, generated by ./test/scripts/test_gen
		
	./test/MockScanner.cpp
		- Mock scanner class for PalParser unit tests

	./test/test_cases/*
		- Test PAL programs (files starting with b are invalid programs)

	./test/test_cases/checkpoint_1/*
		- Test PAL programs for checkpoint 1 submission

	./test/test_cases/future_tests/*
		- Test PAL programs for semantic errors not relavent to checkpoint 1

	./test/test_cases/stress_tests/*
		- Test PAL programs that take a while to parse

	./test/test_cases/stress_tests/*
		- Test PAL programs that take a while to parse

